    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>June 27&#47;51</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir Your favor<lb/> of <date>10th</date> inst has been some time received.<lb/> I have been obliged to leave town for<lb/> some days since it reached me&#44; or I would<lb/> have received my earlier attention. I<lb/> have collected &#36;9 from <persName>A Moise Inn</persName> &#38;<lb/> will send to <persName>Mrs Griswold</persName> for the amt<lb/> due from her. <persName>Mr Joshua Lazarus</persName> as<lb/> you are doubtless aware has left for<lb/> <placeName>Europe</placeName>. I ascertain thus far that<lb/> <persName>Mrs M L Cohen</persName><lb/>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<persName>John I. Cohen</persName><lb/>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<persName>Leopold Cohn</persName><lb/> <persName>Col M Jacobs</persName><lb/> are <hi rend="underline">not</hi> subscribers to the Occident. My<lb/> friend <persName>P Wineman</persName> did not desire it<lb/> either&#44; but &#40;to please me I think&#41; has<lb/> concluded to take it for the year at<lb/> any rate. <persName>Mr B D Lazarus</persName><lb/>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#38; <persName>B Mordecai</persName><lb/> <hi rend="underline">marked with a star</hi> in yr list&#44; I have<lb/> not yet seen. I have not had time<lb/> to solicit new subscribers&#44; but yr list<lb/> is so full already in <placeName>Charleston</placeName>&#44; that<lb/> I know of few others to whom<lb/> application could be made. In the</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>cases of the 4 persons before named who<lb/> decline the Occident&#44; I have not been<lb/> able to get numbers back. Some say<lb/> they did not get but <hi rend="underline">one</hi> number&#44;<lb/> &#38; others that what they did get were<lb/> ret<hi rend="underline">d</hi> &#38;c &#38;c I will endeavor to <hi rend="underline">retain</hi><lb/> <persName>B Mordecai</persName> &#38; <persName>B D Lazarus</persName> if possible<lb/> I learn from <persName>David Lopez</persName>&#44; <persName>M H Nathan</persName><lb/> <persName>M D Hyams</persName> &#38; <persName>N A Cohen</persName> that their<lb/> withdrawal from yr subscription roll<lb/> originated from no objection to yr course<lb/> The two first did not want it &#38; had<lb/> no time to read it &#38; the two last had<lb/> copies in their houses taken by their<lb/> sons. I will inquire of <persName>Jackson Moses</persName><lb/> whether he considers himself a subscriber<lb/> or&#44; also of <persName>I. L. DeLange</persName> &#38; <persName>J. Harris</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">If anything can be done for the<lb/> Prayers &#38; Bible or Occident&#44; I will<lb/> endeavor to accomplish it during<lb/> the ensuing dull season.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Yr Occident for <date>July</date> is at hand<lb/> It bears down manfully upon the<lb/> disorganizing clique who now rule<lb/> our congregational matters without<lb/> religion&#44; without order &#38; without<lb/> law.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">It must do the Occident good with</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>Israelites <hi rend="underline">generally</hi>&#44; &#39;altho with some of<lb/> the straggling followers of the now<lb/> dethroned <persName>Posnanski</persName> dissatisfaction<lb/> may be created</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Of course this &#40;the <hi rend="underline">good</hi>&#44;&#41; is not the object&#44; but<lb/> I for one will not object if it prove an<lb/> <hi rend="underline">incident</hi> to the publications referred<lb/> to.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have to return you the regards<lb/> &#38; good wishes of the individuals&#44;<lb/> to whom you desired remembrance<lb/> &#38; subscribe myself</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Yrs Truly &#38;c</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Thos J Moise</persName></p>
          
        </body>
